  "prompt": "Should organic peanut butter be refrigerated?",
  "response": "Organic peanut butter does not necessarily need to be refrigerated, but doing so can help extend its shelf life and maintain freshness. Most commercial organic peanut butters contain only peanuts and possibly salt, which means they can typically be stored in a cool, dark place, like a pantry, for several months. However, if the peanut butter is natural and does not contain preservatives, refrigeration can help prevent the oils from separating and keep it from going rancid. Always check the label for specific storage recommendations, and if you prefer a creamier texture, you might want to stir it well after refrigeration.",
